pullRequest.body:
+ Add lemmas about integrality and membership in an subalgebra of inverse elements.

+ As a consequence, show the integral closure of a field in a division ring is an intermediate field `IntermediateField.algClosure`.

+ Golf some lemmas along the way.

I've been able to show this @MichaelStollBayreuth
Very nice!

These porting notes seem to be decidedly unhelpful without knowing what the original proof was...
Can we just remove them?
Probably they mean that there exist some shorter proof that times out, so they have more than zero information content ... I'll take a look at the original proof in mathlib3.
Oh, this is actually a proof I golfed. Will remove the porting notes then!
Why `letI` and not just `let`? (As far as I know, in Lean 4, the `I` is no longer related to instances, but now means "inline".)

```suggestion
  let := divisionRingOfFiniteDimensional F K; H.isUnit
```

```suggestion
/-- A commutative domain that is an integral algebra over a field is a field. -/
```

Hi @adamtopaz Do you think (1) this name is good, (2) the argument order is okay (or do you prefer `Place R K`)? This file actually imports TopologicalSpace so we could define the topology on this type, but it's already almost 1000 lines, so maybe put that into another file that constructs the LocallyRingedSpace / Scheme (transc. deg. 1 case) instances.

```suggestion
  let _ := divisionRingOfFiniteDimensional F K; H.isUnit
```
What about `IntermediateField.integralClosure`? The name `algClosure` looks a little strange.

It's a bit strange to talk about the integral closure when you know it's a field. There are [AlgebraicClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsAlgClosed/AlgebraicClosure.html#AlgebraicClosure) and [IsAlgClosure](https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/Mathlib/FieldTheory/IsAlgClosed/Basic.html#IsAlgClosure) in mathlib, and I like the shorter name.

In Mathlib, we have `separableClosure` as the relative separable closure (an intermediate field) and `SeperableClosure` as the absolute separable closure. And `normalClosure` for relative normal closure. Do you think `algebraicClosure` is a good name?
Okay, even though there are IsSepClosed/Closure and IsAlgClosed/Closure, I think we should follow s/SeparableClosure and AlgebraicClosure here to name this algebraicClosure as you said.
Can you use at least `variable {R S : Type*}` at the beginning of the section?
What about splitting this part to another PR? It seems quite unrelated to the rest.
This would make sense; perhaps in a new file, maybe `Mathlib.RingTheory.Valuation.Place` (together with the definition of the topology on `Place K R`)? (See the comment on lines +38 to +42.)
Sorry for the delay; I've removed `Place` from this PR and fixed merge conflicts, and the PR now finally passed CI.

```suggestion
/-- The integral closure of `R` in an `R`-algebra `A`. -/
```
I'm not sure if the `algClosure` part is accurate.
Good catch, thanks!

```suggestion
/-- The algebraic closure of a field `K` in an extension `L`, the subalgebra `integralClosure K L`
upgraded to an intermediate field (when `K` and `L` are both fields). -/
```
